Astrea of the Stars 04-Aug-21 11:26 PM
It's a standard library... huh. The inside of the room looks like a legitimate library - the walls are a nice brown, shelves cover the entire place, and there's even a desk and all where the librarian would be (obviously, there are no librarians, though there are some nice office supplies here. No computers, though). Looking at the shelves... you're somewhat surprised to see that the books are mostly normal. Nothing about any of them particularly stands out as 'Killing Game'-y to you, all being pretty standard books you would have (no NSFW books, though). Well, there is one book of interest. Or, rather, there's a ripped-out page on the ground from an old book - it seems to be the front page of said book, just beyond the quote they put at the beginning of pretty much every book these days. It simply states that the title is "The History of the Gods' Killing Game". No author has been provided. Huh. You get the feeling no one in this entire bunker knows what that means. Not even the hosts. ...also, there's a book about Charles Darwin and evolution right next to it, but that means nothing. (edited)
